Hello for all great students in Magshimim class

What does it do?
=================
This python projects is helping for testing Whatsapp server you just finished to coding.
In consts.py you will find the server address and port, the default address is 127.0.0.1:8826, fill free to change as
you need, remember to change it also in the server side

What the tests check?
======================
The test is checking basic functionality of the Whatsapp server, and simulates multiple users.
It adding 3 new users, validates all users are exist in each client,
and finally sending message between 2 users, and validates that message has been received by 2 end-users.

How to run this test?
=====================
Requirement:
1. The project was tested with python 3.7.4. It can also worked on other python versions.
Download latest python version for windows from: https://www.python.org/downloads/

2. This project uses python package called termcolor to print colorful output
    use this command to install: pip install termcolor
    cannot find pip exception: Try to use google to solve you issue, and after it install termcolor

3. In order to see the colorful output- you need to run it with ipython.
    install ipython (powerful python interpreter): pip install ipython

How to run?
The main function is in tests.py.
Execute in elevated cmd:
    Right click on cmd.exe -> "Run as Administrator". Then execute "ipython tests.py"

What to expect?
The test has indicative message. If all is good expect "Good Job :)" in the end.
You shouldn't see any exception in the output.
Example output is in output_example.txt file

